Right now, there are only two places you can watch Titan sports. Football is on Striv and volleyball is on Mr. Dermody‚Äôs YouTube channel. We hope to consolidate that by winter sports but technical requirements of the gym camera are holding us back. If we are able to find people (preferably students, wink, wink) to announce home volleyball games, we‚Äôll move that to Striv.

There has been a rise in fake events on Facebook saying they‚Äôre broadcasting our games. They aren‚Äôt. Please be cautious when sharing or engaging with those events. Reach out if you have questions!

Jones is set to continue his Academic studies and Football career at the University of Iowa. #LCSportsfanTitans #lctitans

shared_text:
Lewis Central Lucky Children
May 23 at 9:19 AM ¬∑

Hopefully everyone has seen the last communication from DK. We are moving ahead to reopen on June 22 for summer. I am just now getting a feel for the numbers interested and will have final restrictions from the state for June next week. Every option avail to us will be used BUT we are working thru the 5 pages of restrictions that are currently in place.

Unfortunatly family's that attend will be charged full time weekly rates whether they are in attendance or not. We will most definitely have to limit the number of students. We will not be able to accept any new enrollments and the full time, full year students will be admitted first. . We want to be sure we open up to as many as we can handle safely. Yes, our program will look very different with no field trips, swimming and play equip. Hopefully those restrictions are waived soon. Please be assured if you can find other arrangements for summer, your position for the fall will still be available. If you have any questions, please feel free to email me.

I am just now getting a feel for the numbers interested and will have final restrictions from the state for June next week. Every option avail to us will be used BUT we are working thru the 5 pages of restrictions that are currently in place.

Unfortunatly family's that attend will be charged full time weekly rates whether they are in attendance or not. We will most definitely have to limit the number of students. We will not be able to accept any new enrollments and the full time, full year students will be admitted first. . We want to be sure we open up to as many as we can handle safely. Yes, our program will look very different with no field trips, swimming and play equip. Hopefully those restrictions are waived soon. Please be assured if you can find other arrangements for summer, your position for the fall will still be available. If you have any questions, please feel free to email me.

shared_text:
Lewis Central Mobile Food Pantry
April 25 at 8:00 PM ¬∑

The April 28 Food Pantry will again be hosted at Lewis Central High School, 3504 Harry Langdon Blvd.
-The Food Pantry entry will be at the high school ONLY. Please follow directions of staff and the Council Bluffs Police Department. Following directions will allow the line to move faster.
-You are not allowed to get out of your car. Staff will bring the food to your car and place it in your trunk or hatchback. Following guidelines by health experts and the Food Bank, we want to limit contact between staff and participants.
-The Food Bank for the Heartland has pre-packaged boxes that will be distributed. ONE BOX will be handed out PER CAR regardless of how many families are in the car. If you need more than one box, you will need to get back in line. We will not hold boxes.
-We will begin 30 minutes earlier than usual, at 4:00 pm.
-We will be loading ten cars at a time, twice as many as March. Paying attention and following the directions of staff will allow the line to move as efficiently as possible. We appreciate your cooperation!

LC Booster Club
April 8 at 11:52 AM ¬∑

Thank you to everyone who donated and purchased tickets for the 2020 Lewis Central Booster Club Auction. We decided to postpone the event due to ongoing concerns about COVID-19 and the extension of the social distancing ban. This was not a decision we entered into lightly, but one we felt was necessary for the health and safety of our community.

As of now we don't have a definite date for the new event, but we hope you will plan to join us in the future. In the meantime, we're working to refund all existing ticket holders as well as contact any businesses or organizations that donated items with expirations. If you have any questions, please contact Shellie Schultz, committee chair, at skschultz@live.com.

Thriving Titans LC
April 2 at 6:54 PM ¬∑

Look at what we are able to do because of ALL OF YOU!!

Thriving Titans has continued serving the Lewis Central community in recent weeks by providing food pantry services and weekend backpacks. With the upcoming holiday weekend right around the corner, the need for nutritional support increases. Because of the continued support and generosity of our community, Thriving Titans was able to prepare TWO HUNDRED bags of food to support families over the long weekend. In addition, we will be sending weekend backpacks home with EVERY child (300+) that accesses the free breakfast and lunch program that Lewis Central Schools is currently providing.

This could not have been done without YOU! All of the food and monetary donations from the community have been such a blessing. We simply cannot thank you enough for the continued support of Thriving Titans.

post_text: Planning to attend the Food Pantry tomorrow? Check out the update below!
shared_text:
Lewis Central Mobile Food Pantry
March 23 at 10:00 AM ¬∑

March 24 Food Pantry Update
-The Food Pantry entry will be at the high school ONLY. Please follow directions of staff and the Council Bluffs Police Department. Following directions will allow the line to move faster.
-You are not allowed to get out of your car. Staff will bring the food to your car and place it in your trunk or hatchback. Following guidelines by health experts and the Food Bank, we want to limit contact between staff and participants.
-The Food Bank for the Heartland has pre-packaged boxes that will be distributed. ONE BOX will be handed out PER CAR regardless of how many families are in the car. If you need more than one box, you will need to get back in line. We will not hold boxes.
-We will be loading five cars at a time. Paying attention and following the directions of staff will allow the line to move as efficiently as possible. We appreciate your cooperation!

UPDATE: As of 5:00 pm tonight, this issue was resolved by Windstream. All services should be running normally tomorrow.

9:47 am - our phones are currently down. We are unable to make calls outside the district and calls cannot come in. Our technicians are working on the problem. If you need to contact a staff member, a reminder that many email addresses are on the website staff directory pages.
